The paper discusses the development of a graphical tool for programming robotic tasks and mission control. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) since the tool involves the use of state machines and sophisticated debugging functionality. The paper also mentions the integration of error handling and recovery mechanisms, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of a GUI for visual programming, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
